ncluding working with sponsors;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> It would be helpful to investigate and understand w</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">hy was a Free School that was given approval to open in Slough Berkshire </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">can </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">be allowed to open in Stoke Poges South Buckinghamshire in an area that has no need for school places and a community that does not require a school or have the infrastructure to support an 850 pupil school?</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">16</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7.33pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> July 2012</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> The Secretary of State for Education approves Slough Sikh Education Trust’s application to establish the Khalsa Secondary Academy (KSA) Free School in Slough</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">September/October 2012</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Marketing the school everywhere but South Bucks</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">8</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7.33pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:super">th</span><span st